  "body": "Whenever a developer wants to emit metrics from a new part of Besu, they must first find a way to get the MetricsSystem implementation it is using into the class that has the data being measured.  Currently, the only way to do that is to add a MetricsSystem to the constructor path to every class between the one being measured and another which already has it.  The worst case situation is I have to go all the way back to BesuCommand to get the configured MetricsSystem. \n\nAttached is a text file that shows the subgraph of Besu which must be MetricSystem aware.\n[https://app.zenhub.com/files/206414745/b1fdafad-e11e-491d-8de9-a61b124a6e37/download](https://app.zenhub.com/files/206414745/b1fdafad-e11e-491d-8de9-a61b124a6e37/download)\n\nThe EVMTool already wraps the MetricSystem in a Dagger module. If we push that back up to the metrics gradle module, then BesuCommand or RunnerBuilder could configure that module once, and any class that needs metrics could have it injected via Dagger.",
